Rioting broke out in Toledo, Ohio as counter-protestors clashed with neo-Nazis, leading to chaos in the streets.
The white supremacists aimed to protest black gang violence, sparking outrage and condemnation from local leaders and Holocaust survivors.
A city council candidate withdrew after ties to white supremacists were revealed, while a Republican lawmaker criticized a Black legislative group for alleged racism.
The situation escalated as gangs took advantage of the volatile atmosphere, with residents divided over allowing the march.
Amidst the turmoil, calls for peace and unity emerged to address the underlying issues.
